# Example /etc/crypttab entry for Chapter 5 exercises
# Format: name  UUID=<uuid>  key-file  options
#
# This file is referenced during boot to unlock encrypted devices.
# Place LUKS entries here for automated unlocking.
#
# Field 1: mapped device name (appears as /dev/mapper/<name>)
# Field 2: source device (always use UUID=)
# Field 3: key file path, or "none" for interactive passphrase
# Field 4: options (luks = auto-detect LUKS format)
#
# Example with passphrase prompt at boot:
# secret  UUID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx  none  luks
#
# Example with keyfile (no prompt):
# secret  UUID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx  /root/luks-keyfile  luks
#
# After editing, run: sudo systemctl daemon-reload
# Test without reboot: sudo cryptdisks_start secret
